---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/paths';
---
<style>
.pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 24px; margin-top: 48px; align-items: start; }
.pricing-card { background: var(--white); border-radius: 18px; border: 1.5px solid var(--gray-200); padding: 36px 32px; position: relative; transition: all 0.2s; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.pricing-card:hover { box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(30,58,95,0.1); transform: translateY(-2px); }
.pricing-card.featured { border-color: var(--secondary); box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(74,144,217,0.1), 0 20px 48px rgba(74,144,217,0.1); }
.pricing-badge-pill { position: absolute; top: -14px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); padding: 5px 18px; background: var(--accent); color: var(--primary-dark); border-radius: 20px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; white-space: nowrap; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.pricing-tier-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.pricing-tagline { font-size: 14px; color: var(--gray-500); margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.5; }
.price-big { font-size: 48px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--primary); letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.price-big sup { font-size: 24px; vertical-align: super; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0; }
.price-period { font-size: 14px; color: var(--gray-500); margin-bottom: 6px; }
.price-custom { font-size: 36px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--primary); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.best-for { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-500); background: var(--gray-50); padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 16px 0 24px; line-height: 1.5; }
.best-for strong { color: var(--primary); }
.pricing-cta-btn { display: block; text-align: center; padding: 13px 24px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.15s; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.cta-secondary-btn { background: var(--secondary); color: white; }
.cta-secondary-btn:hover { background: var(--secondary-dark); }
.cta-outline-btn { background: transparent; color: var(--primary); border: 1.5px solid var(--gray-200); }
.cta-outline-btn:hover { border-color: var(--primary); }
.pricing-divider { height: 1px; background: var(--gray-100); margin-bottom: 24px; }
.includes-label { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--gray-300); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.features-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 11px; flex: 1; }
.features-list li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.45; }
.check-y { flex-shrink: 0; width: 16px; height: 16px; border-radius: 50%; background: rgba(74,144,217,0.1); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--secondary); }
.check-y::after { content: '✓'; }
.savings-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 20px; background: var(--gray-50); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px 28px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-100); margin-top: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.savings-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.6; }
.savings-text strong { color: var(--primary); }
.savings-text .strikethrough { text-decoration: line-through; color: var(--gray-500); }
.savings-text .highlight { color: var(--success); font-weight: 700; }
.savings-link { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--secondary); text-decoration: none; white-space: nowrap; }
.compare-wrap { margin-top: 64px; background: white; border-radius: 16px; border: 1.5px solid var(--gray-100); overflow: hidden; }
.compare-head { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.5fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; background: var(--primary); color: white; padding: 18px 24px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; }
.compare-head .feature-col { text-align: left; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; }
.compare-group { grid-column: 1 / -1; padding: 10px 24px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--secondary); background: rgba(74,144,217,0.04); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-100); }
.compare-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.5fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; padding: 12px 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-100); align-items: center; font-size: 13px; text-align: center; }
.compare-row:hover { background: var(--gray-50); }
.compare-feature-name { text-align: left; color: var(--gray-700); }
.compare-yes { color: var(--success); font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; }
.compare-no { color: var(--gray-200); font-size: 16px; }
.compare-partial { color: var(--warning); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; }
.trust-section { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr; gap: 24px; align-items: stretch; margin-top: 40px; }
.trust-panel,
.checkout-panel,
.enterprise-route-panel {
  background: var(--white);
  border: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
  border-radius: 14px;
  padding: 26px;
}
.trust-panel h3,
.checkout-panel h3,
.enterprise-route-panel h3 { font-size: 20px; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 18px; }
.trust-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 14px; }
.trust-card { background: var(--gray-50); border: 1px solid var(--gray-100); border-radius: 12px; padding: 18px; }
.trust-card strong { display: block; color: var(--primary); font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.trust-card p { color: var(--gray-600); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; }
.trust-compact { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 18px; }
.trust-compact span { background: rgba(74,144,217,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(74,144,217,0.18); border-radius: 999px; color: var(--primary); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; padding: 7px 10px; }
.checkout-panel { display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: space-between; }
.checkout-panel p { color: var(--gray-600); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.checkout-note { background: rgba(16,185,129,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(16,185,129,0.18); border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px; color: var(--primary); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; }
.enterprise-route-panel { margin-top: 32px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; gap: 20px; align-items: center; background: var(--primary); border-color: var(--primary); }
.enterprise-route-panel h3 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 8px; }
.enterprise-route-panel p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.74); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; max-width: 740px; }
.faq-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; margin-top: 40px; }
.faq-item { background: white; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-100); padding: 24px; }
.faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 10px; }
.faq-a { font-size: 15px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.7; }
.beta-notice { background: rgba(245,166,35,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(245,166,35,0.25); border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px 24px; margin-top: 40px; display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
.beta-notice-icon { font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; }
.beta-notice-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.65; }
.beta-notice-text strong { color: var(--primary); }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .pricing-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .trust-section,
  .enterprise-route-panel { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .trust-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .compare-head { grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr 1fr; }
  .compare-row { grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr 1fr; }
  .compare-row > *:last-child { display: none; }
  .compare-head > *:last-child { display: none; }
}
</style>

<BaseLayout title="Pricing — Cadence: Transparent Pricing, Replace Five Tools" description="Cadence replaces your fragmented management stack starting at $12/seat/month. Three tiers, full feature comparison, and an honest explanation of what beta access means today." activeNav="pricing">

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href={withBase('/')}>Home</a><span>/</span>Pricing</div>
    <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(245,166,35,0.25);color:var(--accent-light);">Transparent Pricing</div>
    <h1>Replace five tools. <span class="accent">Pay less.</span></h1>
    <p>The average fragmented management stack costs $25–30 per seat per month — across tools that share no data and produce no intelligence. Cadence replaces all of it, starting at $12/seat/month.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section section-light">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="beta-notice">
      <div class="beta-notice-icon">⚡</div>
      <div class="beta-notice-text">
        <strong>About beta pricing:</strong> Cadence is currently in invitation-only beta. The pricing below reflects our general availability targets ($12 / $24 / $48 per seat per month, billed annually). Current beta participants access the platform under early-access terms. We'll provide 90+ days notice before transitioning to GA pricing.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <div class="pricing-card">
        <div class="pricing-tier-name">Essentials</div>
        <div class="pricing-tagline">The management operating plane for teams building their foundation.</div>
        <div class="price-big"><sup>$</sup>12</div>
        <div class="price-period">per seat / month, billed annually</div>
        <div class="best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Organizations of 50–300 people building systematic management practices.</div>
        <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="pricing-cta-btn cta-outline-btn">Request beta access</a>
        <div class="pricing-divider"></div>
        <div class="includes-label">Includes</div>
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> 1:1 Management Engine — structured agendas, AI summaries</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Goals &amp; OKR Tracking — cascaded, live in every 1:1</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Recognition &amp; Rewards — 5:1 ratio tracking</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Survey Engine — pulse, engagement, exit, stay interviews</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Job Architecture — living role definitions</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> AI meeting summaries</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Private AI coaching — manager lane</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Standard integrations (Slack, Google Calendar, Zoom)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-card featured">
        <div class="pricing-badge-pill">⭐ Most Popular</div>
        <div class="pricing-tier-name">Professional</div>
        <div class="pricing-tagline">Full intelligence layer for mid-market People leaders.</div>
        <div class="price-big"><sup>$</sup>24</div>
        <div class="price-period">per seat / month, billed annually</div>
        <div class="best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Organizations of 100–1,000 people where the CHRO needs full Culture Scorecard visibility.</div>
        <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="pricing-cta-btn cta-secondary-btn">Request beta access</a>
        <div class="pricing-divider"></div>
        <div class="includes-label">Everything in Essentials, plus</div>
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> 9-Box Talent Calibration — blind dual-rating, KVD workflows</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> ER Command Center — full case lifecycle</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Full Culture Scorecard — composite org health</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Turnover prediction — AI early warning</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Private AI coaching — manager AND employee lanes</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> L2 manager chain dashboard</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Advanced analytics and reporting</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Priority support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-card">
        <div class="pricing-tier-name">Enterprise</div>
        <div class="pricing-tagline">Full platform with enterprise security, compliance, and dedicated support.</div>
        <div class="price-custom">Custom</div>
        <div class="price-period">500+ seats · Annual contract</div>
        <div class="best-for"><strong>Best for:</strong> Organizations with 500+ employees or complex enterprise security requirements.</div>
        <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="pricing-cta-btn cta-outline-btn">Talk to us</a>
        <div class="pricing-divider"></div>
        <div class="includes-label">Everything in Professional, plus</div>
        <ul class="features-list">
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> SSO / SAML + SCIM provisioning</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Custom HRIS integrations</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Configurable data retention</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Dedicated Customer Success Manager</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> SLA-backed uptime guarantees</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Data Processing Agreement (DPA)</li>
          <li><span class="check-y"></span> Custom onboarding and training</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-section" aria-label="Self-serve trust and checkout details">
      <div class="trust-panel">
        <h3>Buy without wondering what happens to your people data.</h3>
        <div class="trust-grid">
          <div class="trust-card">
            <strong>Human decisions stay human.</strong>
            <p>Cadence surfaces patterns, coaching prompts, and review queues. It does not decide discipline, promotion, termination, compensation, or performance ratings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-card">
            <strong>Your company data is not used for model training by default.</strong>
            <p>Customer audio, transcripts, coaching outputs, survey responses, ER records, performance records, recognition records, and scorecard telemetry are not used to train, fine-tune, or improve Cadence AI models by default, unless your company explicitly agrees in writing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-card">
            <strong>Security review has a path.</strong>
            <p>Essentials and Professional teams can start with standard terms. If you need SSO/SAML, procurement review, a security questionnaire, or enterprise DPA negotiation, route to the Enterprise path.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-compact" aria-label="Trust summary">
          <span>Human-reviewed AI</span>
          <span>No customer-data model training by default</span>
          <span>DPA available for review</span>
          <span>SOC 2 readiness in progress</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="checkout-panel">
        <div>
          <h3>What you get after checkout</h3>
          <p>Cadence provisions your workspace, invites your first admins, and guides your team into the first 1:1 setup flow. Your managers still lead the conversations. Cadence provides the operating system around them: agendas, action items, goals, recognition, coaching prompts, and the Culture Scorecard signals that help leaders see where management is working.</p>
          <div class="checkout-note">AI outputs are decision-support. Formal people decisions stay with accountable humans.</div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0;">Need SSO/SAML, procurement review, a custom DPA, or more than 300 seats? Use the Enterprise path so the right human review happens before purchase.</p>
      </aside>
    </div>
    <div class="enterprise-route-panel">
      <div>
        <h3>Some purchases should not be self-serve.</h3>
        <p>If your team needs SSO/SAML, procurement review, security questionnaires, custom legal review, regulated privacy review, custom privacy deployment, or more than 300 seats, Cadence routes you to an Enterprise path before checkout. Regulated or custom privacy deployments use the Enterprise/legal review path before activating covered features.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px;">Enterprise-shaped intent always routes to a human-led path. Self-serve is for standard Essentials and Professional starts.</p>
      </div>
      <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Talk to Cadence</a>
    </div>
    <div class="savings-row">
      <div class="savings-text">Cadence Professional at 300 seats: <strong>$86,400/year</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Comparable fragmented stack: <span class="strikethrough">$108,000+/year</span> &nbsp; <span class="highlight">You save $21,600+/year — and gain a Culture Scorecard none of them can produce alone.</span></div>
      <a href="#comparison" class="savings-link">See full comparison →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-white" id="comparison">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="center">
      <div class="section-badge">Feature Comparison</div>
      <h2 class="section-headline">Every feature, every tier.</h2>
      <p class="section-subhead">We believe in showing you exactly what you get. No fine print.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-wrap">
      <div class="compare-head">
        <div class="feature-col">Feature</div>
        <div>Essentials</div>
        <div>Professional</div>
        <div>Enterprise</div>
      </div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Core Management</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">1:1 Management Engine</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">AI meeting summaries</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Private AI coaching — manager</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Private AI coaching — employee</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Goals &amp; OKRs</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">OKR cascading (Company → Team → IC)</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Live goal context in 1:1 sidebar</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">AI goal health recommendations</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Talent Calibration</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">9-Box Talent Calibration</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Blind dual-rating (L1 + L2)</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Employee Relations</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">ER Command Center</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">PIP builder with milestones</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Intelligence &amp; Analytics</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Full Culture Scorecard</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Turnover prediction</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Board-ready reporting</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-group">Security &amp; Compliance</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">SOC 2 readiness in progress</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">SSO / SAML</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-yes">✓</div></div>
      <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-feature-name">Data Processing Agreement (DPA)</div><div class="compare-no">—</div><div class="compare-partial">Standard</div><div class="compare-yes">Custom</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-light">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="center">
      <div class="section-badge">Pricing FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="section-headline">Answers to common questions.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What's the difference between beta pricing and GA pricing?</div><div class="faq-a">During beta, access is invitation-only and pricing is discussed individually. The $12 / $24 / $48 tiers reflect our GA targets. We'll provide 90+ days notice before transitioning any beta participant to GA pricing, and beta participants will receive preferential terms.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What's the minimum seat count?</div><div class="faq-a">Essentials starts at 50 seats. Professional starts at 100 seats. Enterprise is custom. If you're below the minimums, reach out anyway.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is there an annual commitment required?</div><div class="faq-a">The published pricing is for annual billing. Monthly billing is available at a 20% premium. Multi-year agreements receive additional discounts.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What tools does Cadence replace?</div><div class="faq-a">Cadence Essentials replaces 15Five (or equivalent), a standalone recognition platform, and your survey tool. Professional adds 9-box calibration, ER case management, and the Culture Scorecard intelligence layer. Most Professional customers consolidate 4–6 tools into one.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do you offer a free trial?</div><div class="faq-a">During beta, access is by invitation only rather than open trial. We offer a live walkthrough with sample data. Once we move to GA, we'll offer a standard free trial.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is Cadence making people decisions with AI?</div><div class="faq-a">No. Cadence uses AI to surface patterns, summarize work, suggest coaching prompts, and route issues for human review. It does not make employment decisions. Discipline, promotion, termination, compensation, performance ratings, and formal ER actions require accountable human judgment and normal company process.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What happens to 1:1 notes and meeting data?</div><div class="faq-a">1:1 notes, transcripts, summaries, coaching outputs, goals, recognition, survey signals, ER records, and scorecard telemetry are used to deliver Cadence to your company. They are not used to train, fine-tune, or improve Cadence AI models by default, unless your company explicitly agrees in writing.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Does audio recording start automatically?</div><div class="faq-a">No. Audio capture is optional and consent-gated. Cadence is useful with or without audio: the operating plane still supports agendas, action items, goals, recognition, surveys, ER workflows, and scorecard signals.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can we buy self-serve before a full security review?</div><div class="faq-a">Essentials and Professional are built for teams that can start from standard terms and standard controls. If your purchase requires security review, procurement, SSO/SAML, custom legal terms, regulated privacy review, custom privacy deployment, or more than 300 seats, Cadence routes you to Enterprise before checkout.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is a DPA available?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes, a DPA review path is part of the buying motion. If your deployment requires a DPA before employee personal data is processed, use the Enterprise/legal review path before activating covered features.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How does Cadence use manager taxonomy?</div><div class="faq-a">Cadence looks for management behavior patterns across operational signals such as 1:1 cadence, follow-through, recognition, goals, ER outcomes, and eligible aggregate survey signals. Taxonomy outputs are decision-support for trained human review. They are not automated employment decisions.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are survey comments attached to managers?</div><div class="faq-a">No. Open-text survey themes are used only after Cadence's anonymity and de-identification thresholds are met. Raw open text is not surfaced in manager taxonomy review packets.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

